\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 Having had a war literature, we now face the period in which is to be born a post-war literature.}{\f0\fs24\b0  It is a common thought among people everywhere that during the years between 1914 and 1918 the elements melted with fervent heat. The old world has been done away, and all things are ready to be made new. The outlines of seas and continents are the same as before, but the viewpoint, outlook, and general consciousness of the race are totally changed. It could hardly seem more so if we had been bodily transported to another planet. The new age will express itself in a new literature\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a reconstruction literature.}{ }
